'8:30': [
{sup:1, word:"heavens", lines:["Solomon prayed that God would hear from His dwelling place in the heavens the supplication offered to Him by His people when they prayed toward the temple as His dwelling place on the earth. This indicates that God has two dwelling places, one in the heavens and one on the earth. Actually, these two are one; they are the two ends of God&rsquo;s one dwelling place. Today the believers in Christ as God&rsquo;s dwelling place ({Eph2:21|Eph. 2:21}-{Eph2:22|22}) are a particular people, a people who are in the heavens and on the earth ({Eph2:6|Eph. 2:6}; {Col3:1|Col. 3:1}-{Col3:3|3}). See {Gen28:17^1|note 17<sup>1</sup>} in {Gen28|Gen. 28}."]},
],
