'8:59': [
{sup:1, word:"cause", lines:["For God to maintain the cause of His people means that He executes justice regarding their situation. Throughout the centuries God has maintained the cause of His people Israel. When they were wrong with Him, He chastised them and disciplined them through the hands of the Gentile powers, including the Babylonian, Persian, Grecian, and Roman empires. But when these nations went too far in dealing with Israel, God maintained Israel&rsquo;s cause, punishing those who mistreated them (see {Isa10:5^1|note 5<sup>1</sup>} in {Isa10|Isa. 10} and {Isa26:13^1P1|note 13<sup>1</sup>, par. 1}, in {Isa26|Isa. 26}). This indicates that behind the physical realm there is the spiritual realm, in which God governs the entire universe, executing justice for His people every day as each day requires. God does this for His elect, for both Israel and the believers in Christ ({1Pe4:17|1&nbsp;Pet. 4:17} and {1Pe4:17^1|note 1})."]},
],
